 The Business Development role is responsible for expanding Sitel‚Äôs business by prospecting, developing and managing potential new clients. The ideal candidate will have a strong background and demonstrated experience in the Business Process Outsourcing (BPO) space working with senior level decision makers. He/she will have a unique ability to build relationships and develop networks. 
 This individual will focus on top domestic and global companies. This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced sales professional to bring his/her unique set of skills and relationships to a dynamic company. This individual will develop proactive proposals and win strategies, respond to RFI/RFP‚Äôs with offers of contact center services as well as sell value add products and services. This could also include selling opportunities into the EMEA market for our North American based global clients. 
 
 Key Responsibilities: 
 
 Drive the sales strategy and process from plan to close, justifying account qualification and designing win strategies 
 Follow the sales process to ensure quality and effective win strategies in all proposals regarding content, pricing, solution, and other components as well as creating a competitive analysis 
 Clearly articulate the distinct aspects of products and services 
 
 Experience: 
 
 5 or more year of BPO sales experience. Industry experience with a successful track record collaborating with world-class organizations to offer strategic solutions that deliver results. 
 Experience in selling ‚Äútraditional‚Äù contact center outsourcing services, non-contact center outsourcing experiences (back office, IT service), as well as digital technology and/or consulting services. 
 Must have experience presenting alone in front of potential client executives. 
 Demonstrated experience leading sales opportunities, developing client-focused, differentiated and achievable solutions. 
 
 Skills/Knowledge/Abilities: 
 
 Demonstrates confidence throughout the selling cycle through collaboration. 
 Drive the sales strategy through relationships and process from plan to close. 
 Demonstrates empathy and kindness in everyday performance which enhances sales capability. 
 Proven ability to position products against competitors. 
 Consistently achieve revenue targets in line with team/organizational objectives. 
 Excellent listening, negotiation, presentation (RFP response & proposals) and facilitation skills. 
 Excellent verbal and written communications skills. 
 
 Education: 
 
 Four-year college degree in a business-related field or equivalent industry experience. 
 
 Travel Required: 
 
 75% or more domestic and international travel- post Covid when restrictions are lifted 
 
